RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 21828. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNCLE SINGH raced off the top two, made a three wide bid at the quarter pole, took command in the stretch and finished ridden out. SARAH'S BOY BLUE vied outside of rival around the turn and failed to be a match when the winner took over past upper stretch. HIGGAM dueled inside in early stages and around the turn then weakened in the lane. EDGY LOVER raced three to four wide off the pace and failed to rally. QUARTERNIGHT failed to move into close contention. SHERLOCK WHO raced two to three wide around the turn and failed to threaten. BABYS TIME TO SING showed brief interest then steadily faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 16397. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 12, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Multiple Winners Preferred) .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORTH SIDE set the pace along the inside and held on in final strides. LOVER BOY raced in contention, launched a three wide bid at the quarter pole and was getting to the winner in final stages. RED WHITE AND LOUD raced off the pace, came four wide into the lane and failed to impact the top pair. MR FROST raced five wide into the lane and failed to make an impact. ACE GILFORD raced up close in early stages then faded in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: North Side
ENTRY.OWNER: Seven Arms Stable and Condon Schuyler

ENTRY.NAME: Lover Boy
ENTRY.OWNER: Kennedy Brent A Kennedy Susan K Little Elk Wanda and Kennedy Jr William

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26820. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEA ME BE raced in contention, made a three wide bid at the quarter pole, rallied through the stretch and got up in time. CROCODILE TEARS vied inside rival for the early lead, took command in the stretch and got caught on the wire. CONTRABANDISTA raced up close around the turn, made a move along the inside entering the lane and stayed on for a share. TAP THAT DIAL was not too far back early on, came four to five wide into the lane and lacked a rally. UXMAL vied outside of rival through early stages then gaveway in the lane. ASSET BASIS raced two to three wide and failed to threaten. CODE ONE failed to menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 14100. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HACKER vied inside of MO CHOCTOW for the lead in opening stages, battled on into the lane, dug in gamely, took the edge and held on. MO CHOCTAW dueled outside of HACKER for the lead in early stages, fought back heads apart into the stretch, continued to put in a good effort but could not match strides in final stages. MONTEREY PENINSULA settled off the early pace, made a four wide bid turning for home, rallied through the stretch and gained to the wire. CALLE DE BOYD raced near midpack, came three wide into the lane and failed to kick on. ROBUST was not too fra bcak in early stages, swung two wide into the lane and failed to make an impact. LURCH raced in the back, saved ground and never threatened. PRAIRIE WOLF raced in early contention along the inside, began to flatten midway around the turn and steadily weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Hacker
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, dug in gamely, lasted

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 43047. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TARA'S TIME tracked the pace along the inside, tipped two wide and headed into action at the head of the lane, dug in determinedly and prevailed. BE SINCERE raced off the early leaders, swung five wide entering the lane and finished strongly through the lane. STARGRAZER led the way in early stages, continued to lead the way with a furlong left to run then got wore down late. KAMEA raced in early contention, launched a bid at the quarter pole, stayed on three wide but had no late kick. MY FOUR POINT OH hustled up four wide around the turn and failed to stay on in the lane. KYLIES HOPE settled along the inside, angled two wide for the drive and weakened in the lane. REVENANT raced in or near the back and never menaced.

ENTRY.NAME: Tara's Time
ENTRY.COMMENT: track inside, tipped 2wd upper, drew clear

ENTRY.NAME: Kylies Hope

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 42820. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIAL SUM IN was allowed to settled three to four wide through early stages, picked up the pace and swung five wide into the lane, shifted in a couple paths and drew clear. CREME DE CASSIS dueled for the early lead, battled on into the stretch, fought back three to four wide then got outkicked by the winner. SWEET STROLL was unhurried and raced in the back, saved ground, got going in the stretch run and finished strongly. MOLLY BYE O raced three wide in early contention, sustained bid into upper stretch then weakened. APRETTYLULABY raced in range between foes around the turn then faded in the lane. NATIVE QUEEN vied along the inside in opening stages, stayed up close around the turn, fought back along the inside past upper stretch then came up empty. UNGLUED chased along the inside and steadily fdaed. GOOD N LUCKY raced off the pace, saved ground around the turn, came three wide into the lane and failed to make an impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 13600. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 12, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FASCINATED led the way in opening stages, set the pace around the turn, continued to fend off challengers through the lane and finished well clear. ROCK CITY ROCKET tracked the leader into the turn, hustled along three wide into the lane, sustained through the stretch run and held place. CAPTAIN DON raced up close in early stages, came three wide into the lane, continued in range but lacked the needed kick to reach the top pair. OSCAR WINNER WALLY raced near midpack and four wide around the turn, came wide into the lane and needed more for impact. WESTA WAVERLY raced off the early leaders, hustled along two wide into the lane, gained closer contention but failed to sustain bid. MAFIA DON came away awkwardly at the start and failed to move into contention. A. K. SAFARI raced off the pace, saved ground entering the lane and never threatened.
